 1: # Google Calendar & Gmail MCP - Project Guidelines
 2: 
 3: ## Auth & Development
 4: 
 5: **OAuth Setup** (test mode):
 6: ```bash
 7: export ACCOUNT_MODE=test CALENDARMCP_TOKEN_PATH=~/.config/google-calendar-mcp/tokens.json
 8: npm run auth  # Creates tokens.json; repeat for multiple accounts
 9: npm run verify-tokens  # Verify auth status
10: ```
11: 
12: **Gmail Tokens:**
13: ```bash
14: node auth-gmail.mjs  # Creates tokens-gmail.json (separate from calendar)
15: node check-gmail.mjs  # Quick unread count
16: ```
17: 
18: **Development:**
19: ```bash
20: npm install | npm run build | npm run dev | npm test
21: ```
22: 
23: **Auth Details:**
24: - Tokens stored in `~/.config/google-calendar-mcp/tokens.json` (calendar) and `tokens-gmail.json` (Gmail)
25: - `ACCOUNT_MODE` selects which account; TokenManager auto-refreshes 5 min before expiry
26: - Test tokens expire after 7 days; set env vars before `npm run auth` or in `claude_desktop_config.json`
27: - Token files use 0600 permissions; TokenManager (src/auth/tokenManager.ts) handles multi-account lifecycle
28: 
29: **Test Status:**
30: - ✅ Core handler tests (CreateEventHandler, GetEventHandler, GetCurrentTimeHandler)
31: - ✅ Type-safe content assertions using `{ type: 'text'; text: string }` instead of `as any`
32: - ✅ Integration tests for conflict detection via MCP protocol (real server, real API)
33: - ✅ 486/486 tests passing
34: 
35: ## Script Development
36: 
37: **Code Quality:**
38: - `npm run check-duplicates` — Detect repeated code blocks (scans src/ with 6-line window)
39: 
40: **Avoid bash heredocs with pipes** (causes "parse error near |'"):
41: - Use Write tool or create `.mjs` files in project root instead of `/tmp`
42: - `/tmp` scripts can't access `node_modules`; use project root for npm imports
43: - If using heredoc, keep it simple (no pipes, special chars, or complex syntax)
44: 
45: **Code Quality:**
46: - Avoid dead variables; use derived values instead
47: - Remove comments that duplicate code (keep only non-obvious WHY)
48: - Extract repeated patterns into shared utilities
49: - Use named constants instead of magic strings
50: - Don't mutate input params; create local copies
51: - Prefer direct operations over redundant existence checks (TOCTOU)
52: - Array.slice() naturally clamps; Math.min unnecessary
53: 
54: ## Email Organization System
55: 
56: Core pattern: Label → conditional archive (keep future events, important items, archive routine notifications).
57: 
58: **Key Scripts:**
59: ```bash
60: node list-unread-emails.mjs           # Summary by category/sender
61: node summarize-remaining.mjs          # Remaining uncategorized (internal work, forums)
62: node describe-internal.mjs            # Detailed breakdown of internal team emails (Chandra, Jordan, John, Alex)
63: node create-remaining-filters.mjs     # Create filters (Product Updates, Communities, Services)
64: node apply-filters-to-unread.mjs      # Apply filters to current unread
65: node protect-important-inbox.mjs      # Protect: Cloudflare alerts, Calendly, Capital City Village, Investment Banking
66: node filter-events-by-date.mjs        # Events: future=keep, past=archive
67: node archive-signoz-dmarc.mjs         # Monitoring/DMARC auto-archive
68: ```
69: 
70: **Categories:**
71: | Type | Treatment | Senders/Items |
72: |------|-----------|---|
73: | Protected | Never archive | Cloudflare rate limits, Calendly support, CCV services, IB meetings |
74: | Events | Future keep, past archive | International House, Meetup, Eventbrite, Calendly reminders |
75: | Monitoring | Archive | SigNoz alerts, DMARC reports |
76: | Product Updates | Label + archive | Google Cloud/Workspace, HubSpot, OpenAI, Postman, Resend, Yodlee, Adapty, DataHub |
77: | Communities | Keep | Women Techmakers |
78: | Services | Archive | FoundersCard, Link, Heroku, Zapier, Zillow |
79: | Billing | Conditional | GW invoices, GC charges (rate-limit aware) |
80: 
81: **Shared Utilities:**
82: - `lib/gmail-client.mjs` - Authenticated Gmail client factory; use `createGmailClient()` in all scripts (✅ Applied to 65+ scripts)
83: - `lib/gmail-label-utils.mjs` - Label resolution utilities (NEW - see L6 below)
84:   - `buildLabelCache(gmail)` - Fetch all labels once at startup
85:   - `resolveLabelId(gmail, labelName, labelCache)` - Cached single label lookup
86:   - `resolveLabelIds(gmail, labelNames)` - Batch label resolution
87: - `lib/gmail-batch.mjs` - Batch filter operations for 10-100x speedup
88: - `lib/date-based-filter.mjs` - Pure utility for date parsing (ISO, US, text, weekday patterns; no mutations)
89: 
90: **Code Quality:**
91: - **Established patterns:** Refactored scripts use best practices (error handling, named constants, getHeader() helpers, parallel `Promise.all` for list + detail fetches)
92: - **Performance:** Use `Promise.all` for concurrent list + detail fetches (not serial loops)
93: - **L6 Pattern (NEW):** Dynamic label ID resolution for portability across accounts
94:   - See `docs/LABEL-RESOLUTION-GUIDE.md` for complete pattern documentation
95:   - Replace hardcoded `Label_N` IDs with `labelCache.get('Label/Name')`
96:   - Enables scripts to work across different Gmail accounts with different label IDs
